http://www.bbc.com/culture/story/20130509-dancing-for-peace-in-the-mid-east
Ballroom dancing teacher Pierre Dulaine's return to Jaffa in Israel is chronicled in the new document
“Ballroom dance teaches these children life skills: etiquette, discipline, self-esteem, most importantly, self-respect, respect for your partner,” says Dulaine.The film screened in the Tribeca Film Festival and now the producer of this documentary wants to make a feature film version of Dulaine’s adventures in Israel, to bring to audiences around the world what many regard as a truly inspirational story.Tom Brook reports.